dotnet new console --framework net9.0
dotnet nuget add source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json -n nuget.org
dotnet nuget enable source nuget.org
dotnet nuget list source
dotnet nuget locals all --clear
dotnet restore .\Bing-custom.csproj
dotnet add .\Bing-custom.csproj package Azure.Identity --source nuget.org
dotnet add .\Bing-custom.csproj package DotNetEnv     --source nuget.org
dotnet list .\Bing-custom.csproj package
dotnet build .\Bing-custom.csproj

There are 5 ways to run:
1> dotnet run  .\Bing-custom.csproj
This is default to use serviceprincipal.

2> dotnet run .\Bing-custom.csproj -- --mode azurecli
This uses azure CLI.

3> dotnet run .\Bing-custom.csproj -- --mode interactive
This is interactive mode, however my testing was not successful with this mode.

4> dotnet run .\Bing-custom.csproj -- --mode serviceprincipal
This uses serviceprincipal as well. 

5> dotnet run .\Bing-custom.csproj -- --mode managedidentity
This mode uses managed identity. However, this method will not work in local laptop. It only works in Azure hosted resources.
